ersion":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ab","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What This System Does","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1509601469,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-5028.03515625,"width":177.01487731933594},{"seed":898798493,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"TZxtrqUu0IbIPf8nSsl1t","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"A Job Scheduler System is a distributed platform for defining, scheduling,\nand reliably executing tasks at specified times or intervals. Think of it as\ncron at cloud scale, used by systems like AWS EventBridge, LinkedIn Azkaban,\nand Airbnb Airflow. Job owners register tasks with a cron expression, one-time\ntimestamp, or event trigger. The platform fires every job at exactly the right\nmoment, dispatches it to worker pools, tracks execution state, and handles\nfailures — without missing a fire or running any job twice.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ac","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"A Job Scheduler System is a distributed platform for defining, scheduling,\nand reliably executing tasks at specified times or intervals. Think of it as\ncron at cloud scale, used by systems like AWS EventBridge, LinkedIn Azkaban,\nand Airbnb Airflow. Job owners register tasks with a cron expression, one-time\ntimestamp, or event trigger. The platform fires every job at exactly the right\nmoment, dispatches it to worker pools, tracks execution state, and handles\nfailures — without missing a fire or running any job twice.","height":122.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1557366163,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-5002.03515625,"width":536.54937744140625},{"seed":1486362621,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"JG5mLQrWXq3AdjpTK-4Nz","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Key Challenges","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ad","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key Challenges","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":809472285,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-4852.03515625,"width":104.39993286132812},{"seed":489558109,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"7x_n-M9e0oM24scbj49mr","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Leader election determines which node owns the scheduler clock; lose the\nleader and you miss fire events. Exactly-once execution requires idempotency\nacross scheduler restart, worker crash, and network partition — naive systems\ndouble-fire on every failover. Backpressure prevents flooding queues when\nthousands of jobs trigger at the same cron boundary simultaneously. DAG\ndependency tracking must propagate upstream failures without orphaned waits.\nSub-second p99 latency at 5,000 fires\/sec demands careful time partitioning.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ae","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Leader election determines which node owns the scheduler clock; lose the\nleader and you miss fire events. Exactly-once execution requires idempotency\nacross scheduler restart, worker crash, and network partition — naive systems\ndouble-fire on every failover. Backpressure prevents flooding queues when\nthousands of jobs trigger at the same cron boundary simultaneously. DAG\ndependency tracking must propagate upstream failures without orphaned waits.\nSub-second p99 latency at 5,000 fires\/sec demands careful time partitioning.","height":122.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":571693875,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-4826.03515625,"width":540.48333740234375},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"af","backgroundColor":"#252838","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"TyQ6r903Y8VFdDXWjqM99","x":-428,"seed":1629879485,"boundElements":[],"y":-4680.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":52,"width":888,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1070163325},{"seed":1277254941,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"O3_2Tl8X-pUyql5Nnb8NM","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":14,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Key insight: The hardest problem is exactly-once execution under simultaneous\nscheduler and worker failure. Naive distributed schedulers double-fire on every failover.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"ag","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key insight: The hardest problem is exactly-once execution under simultaneous\nscheduler and worker failure. Naive distributed schedulers double-fire on every failover.","height":35,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#9AA0B4","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":134708435,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-418,"angle":0,"y":-4672.03515625,"width":591.45721435546875},{"seed":361869693,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"AHM59cjEygu6Eq_h0idoF","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArro