,"text":"Category: CPU + Coordination","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4s","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Category: CPU + Coordination","height":15,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#C45C5C","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1979887219,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-1888,"angle":0,"y":-1417.03515625,"width":174.93574523925781},{"seed":206253629,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"spf8kWDoFaPAoTT3bwMtG","strokeWidth":1.5,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":"arrow","opacity":100,"updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[-280,-49.5],[-280,-177]],"version":5,"elbowed":false,"type":"arrow","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4t","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":177,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#C45C5C","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":1671161405,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-1744,"angle":0,"y":-1492.53515625,"width":280},{"seed":245653149,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"6C3-f-JknsRlhr99RKRhs","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[0,620]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4u","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":620,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":556427283,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-464,"angle":0,"y":-1964.03515625,"width":0},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b4v","backgroundColor":"#1E2030","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1.5,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"53dXWRNOvh-aK2dNTODbR","x":-444,"seed":1664647933,"boundElements":[],"y":-1964.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":620,"width":920,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":723392157},{"seed":1854479197,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"D8c8uQCzVe76U1VEWtW6R","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The Two Most Critical Bottlenecks","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4w","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The Two Most Critical Bottlenecks","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":778694067,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1946.03515625,"width":260.7298583984375},{"seed":149399485,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"Z6UMtL3qnoI65O_tim-YG","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The Single Scheduler Node is the most dangerous bottleneck\nbecause it combines three failure modes into one component.\nFirst, it is a CPU bottleneck: the tick loop runs a Postgres SELECT\nscan that grows linearly with the job table. At 500K rows the scan\ntakes roughly 1 second -- exactly equal to the tick interval --\nso the scheduler is permanently behind. From the user's perspective\nthis appears as all jobs firing 2-10 seconds late, then missing\nentire intervals. Second, it is a SPOF: one crash means no jobs\nfire at all, silently, until an operator notices and restarts.\nThird, it is the cause of restart stampedes: on recovery, the\nscheduler sees every missed interval and publishes them all to\nKafka simultaneously, collapsing the worker pool.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4x","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The Single Scheduler Node is the most dangerous bottleneck\nbecause it combines three failure modes into one component.\nFirst, it is a CPU bottleneck: the tick loop runs a Postgres SELECT\nscan that grows linearly with the job table. At 500K rows the scan\ntakes roughly 1 second -- exactly equal to the tick interval --\nso the scheduler is permanently behind. From the user's perspective\nthis appears as all jobs firing 2-10 seconds late, then missing\nentire intervals. Second, it is a SPOF: one crash means no jobs\nfire at all, silently, until an operator notices and restarts.\nThird, it is the cause of restart stampedes: on recovery, the\nscheduler sees every missed interval and publishes them all to\nKafka simultaneously, collapsing the worker pool.","height":195,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":935017213,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1922.03515625,"width":436.6435546875},{"seed":74819613,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"R27LlUQ4eitN3-5RsOV3j","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The Postgres Poll as an IO Bottleneck","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4y","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The Postgres Poll as an IO Bottleneck","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":552058707,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1662.03515625,"width":289.9798583984375},{"seed":1931779197,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"xAyfKXolmCeWMFxgEuYnY","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The O(N) poll scan is subtle because it degrades gradually.\nAt 100K jobs it is invisible. At 500K rows with a covering index\nit takes roughly 800ms. At 1M rows it crosses the 1-second\ntick interval and the scheduler begins missing fire windows.\nWorse, the SELECT acquires row-level read locks that contend\nwith API INSERT transactions, adding latency to job registration.\nUsers registering new jobs experience 2-5 second API timeouts\nprecisely when the system is already under load -- the worst\npossible time. The fix is not a better index; it is replacing\nthe full scan with a pre-sorted time-wheel data structure\nthat makes the next-to-fire lookup O(1) instead of O(N).","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b4z","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The O(N) poll scan is subtle because it degrades gradually.\nAt 100K jobs it is invisible. At 500K rows with a covering index\nit takes roughly 800ms. At 1M rows it crosses the 1-second\ntick interval and the scheduler begins missing fire windows.\nWorse, the SELECT acquires row-level read locks that contend\nwith API INSERT transactions, adding latency to job registration.\nUsers registering new jobs experience 2-5 second API timeouts\nprecisely when the system is already under load -- the worst\npossible time. The fix is not a better index; it is replacing\nthe full scan with a pre-sorted time-wheel data structure\nthat makes the next-to-fire lookup O(1) instead of O(N).","height":178.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":301257565,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1638.03515625,"width":426.5946044921875},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b50","backgroundColor":"#252838","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"pXEnBEjl2qO-8bHXuJpD7","x":-428,"seed":750126301,"boundElements":[],"y":-1428.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":62,"width":888,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":1392139507},{"seed":347824445,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"_tNKWIrNqUa2FLNuwlc8S","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Key insight: All four bottlenecks share a root cause -- the\nscheduler has no partitioning. One node, one scan, one queue,\none worker pool. The fix pattern is always the same: shard.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b51","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key insight: All four bottlenecks share a root cause -- the\nscheduler has no partitioning. One node, one scan, one queue,\none worker pool. The fix pattern is always the same: shard.","height":48.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#9AA0B4","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":907829181,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-418,"angle":0,"y":-1418.03515625,"width":387.62054443359375},{"seed":546714013,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"9Dj8aJzF7EYqFjHi0O_JT","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[3000,0]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b52","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":271074963,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-2424,"angle":0,"y":-1304.03515625,"width":3000},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#3A9E8E","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b53","backgroundColor":"#3A9E8E","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":5,"roundness":null,"type":"ellipse","updated":1773066850103,"id":"EfRuNk4UeFt6sv4L6_tQo","x"