roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"DLQ requires ops runbook; adds human toil on failures","height":16.25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":352454269,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-1940,"angle":0,"y":-256.03515625,"width":341.82162475585938},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b6e","backgroundColor":"#1E2030","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1.5,"version":5,"roundness":null,"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"N_8TbFCcM-qmamAye0Zvz","x":-2356,"seed":289398557,"boundElements":[],"y":-212.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":120,"width":832,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":954559443},{"seed":2005922685,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"BwDENx7hUM-YsIeyX9jQc","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"What We Learned","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6f","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What We Learned","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1129721565,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-2340,"angle":0,"y":-198.03515625,"width":124.66493225097656},{"seed":1470004189,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"lXyTdir2YPs1CCkb3ggL7","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Every upgrade targets exactly one scaling axis. Partitioning removes coordination ceilings.\n32-partition Kafka removes throughput ceilings. Redis lock removes correctness gaps.\nMulti-region removes availability ceilings. Backpressure removes collapse risk.\nThe pattern: measure the binding constraint, apply the minimal surgical fix, re-measure.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6g","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Every upgrade targets exactly one scaling axis. Partitioning removes coordination ceilings.\n32-partition Kafka removes throughput ceilings. Redis lock removes correctness gaps.\nMulti-region removes availability ceilings. Backpressure removes collapse risk.\nThe pattern: measure the binding constraint, apply the minimal surgical fix, re-measure.","height":65,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1737390451,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-2340,"angle":0,"y":-174.03515625,"width":570.04937744140625},{"seed":1501362237,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"e4ZGIg5KDOzJv9jKI-N6S","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[0,1140]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6h","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":1140,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":2043038525,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-464,"angle":0,"y":-1212.03515625,"width":0},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b6i","backgroundColor":"#1E2030","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1.5,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"I0nFx3zH-h_y3JPE-4BLU","x":-444,"seed":655157405,"boundElements":[],"y":-1212.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":1140,"width":920,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":621073171},{"seed":838847741,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"2fPx1mjfOa2gbrNlAXLUH","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Architecture Evolution","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6j","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Architecture Evolution","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":951311261,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1194.03515625,"width":164.32489013671875},{"seed":970401117,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"71o7BseiSj7jYb62uSxNI","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"V1 to V2 was triggered by the O(N) poll scan hitting its ceiling at\n500K jobs. Partitioning the scheduler across 3 nodes by job_id was\nchosen over a faster single node because no machine can scan 10M\nrows in under 1 second. The time-wheel replaces the scan entirely:\neach tick is O(1), checking only the current second bucket in RAM.\nThis brings trigger latency back under 50ms at any job count.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6k","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"V1 to V2 was triggered by the O(N) poll scan hitting its ceiling at\n500K jobs. Partitioning the scheduler across 3 nodes by job_id was\nchosen over a faster single node because no machine can scan 10M\nrows in under 1 second. The time-wheel replaces the scan entirely:\neach tick is O(1), checking only the current second bucket in RAM.\nThis brings trigger latency back under 50ms at any job count.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1103034547,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1170.03515625,"width":431.3525390625},{"seed":300183997,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"NAd3pMiY-lb7GRzqWbxDA","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"V2 to V3 was triggered by dispatch throughput saturating the single\nKafka partition at 1,000 jobs\/s. 32 partitions were chosen because\npartition count directly determines consumer parallelism. Each worker\nowns a disjoint partition subset and processes independently. This\neliminates head-of-line blocking and allows horizontal worker scaling\nwithout any coordination between worker instances.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6l","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"V2 to V3 was triggered by dispatch throughput saturating the single\nKafka partition at 1,000 jobs\/s. 32 partitions were chosen because\npartition count directly determines consumer parallelism. Each worker\nowns a disjoint partition subset and processes independently. This\neliminates head-of-line blocking and allows horizontal worker scaling\nwithout any coordination between worker instances.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":2018533373,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-1032.03515625,"width":439.71148681640625},{"seed":659108381,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"VU1Nsx8ioxEM5XTp9Eupi","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"V3 to V4 was triggered by the first production double-fire on\nscheduler restart. Redis SET NX was chosen over database-level\nuniqueness constraints because the lock must be acquired in a single\nsub-millisecond round-trip before Kafka publish. A Postgres write\nwould add 5-20ms and contend with the job definition table under\nload -- unacceptable at 5,000 dispatches per second.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6m","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"V3 to V4 was triggered by the first production double-fire on\nscheduler restart. Redis SET NX was chosen over database-level\nuniqueness constraints because the lock must be acquired in a single\nsub-millisecond round-trip before Kafka publish. A Postgres write\nwould add 5-20ms and contend with the job definition table under\nload -- unacceptable at 5,000 dispatches per second.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":996371027,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-894.03515625,"width":432.509521484375},{"seed":1190585981,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"MZUfbEMaGDtOJEhNDf8cR","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"V4 to V5 was triggered by a regional AWS outage causing 47 minutes\nof missed fires. Active-passive was chosen over active-active because\ntwo simultaneously active scheduler clusters on the same job set\nrequire distributed consensus on every dispatch decision -- essentially\nbuilding Paxos. Active-passive with a fencing token is sufficient\nto achieve 99.99% and far simpler to operate and reason about.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6n","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"V4 to V5 was triggered by a regional AWS outage causing 47 minutes\nof missed fires. Active-passive was chosen over active-active because\ntwo simultaneously active scheduler clusters on the same job set\nrequire distributed consensus on every dispatch decision -- essentially\nbuilding Paxos. Active-passive with a fencing token is sufficient\nto achieve 99.99% and far simpler to operate and reason about.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":782063709,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-756.03515625,"width":443.79345703125},{"seed":598675165,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"uXXmXLLxtTACZX0-01aTe","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"V5 to Final was triggered by a staging restart stampede. The leaky\nbucket per tenant was chosen over a global rate limit because tenant\nisolation prevents one noisy customer from starving others during\nburst recovery. The worker semaphore provides an absolute concurrency\nceiling -- even under worst-case burst, the pool never exceeds its\ndesigned load, making recovery predictable and bounded.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6o","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"V5 to Final was triggered by a staging restart stampede. The leaky\nbucket per tenant was chosen over a global rate limit because tenant\nisolation prevents one noisy customer from starving others during\nburst recovery. The worker semaphore provides an absolute concurrency\nceiling -- even under worst-case burst, the pool never exceeds its\ndesigned load, making recovery predictable and bounded.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":382248947,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-618.03515625,"width":455.6104736328125},{"seed":469969725,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"CKYMaqXWJAH3_UfCQddTO","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The Pattern: every upgrade in this system follows the same structure.\nIdentify the single binding constraint. Apply the minimal surgical\nchange that removes only that constraint. Verify no new constraint\nis introduced at lower scale than the one just removed. Complexity\nis added one layer at a time, never speculatively. The final system\nis simply V1 sharded at every layer that mattered.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6p","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The Pattern: every upgrade in this system follows the same structure.\nIdentify the single binding constraint. Apply the minimal surgical\nchange that removes only that constraint. Verify no new constraint\nis introduced at lower scale than the one just removed. Complexity\nis added one layer at a time, never speculatively. The final system\nis simply V1 sharded at every layer that mattered.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":359417021,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":-480.03515625,"width":449.53955078125},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b6q","backgroundColor":"#252838","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"QMZayHsiBQaF1HxXvdU46","x":-428,"seed":1079294877,"boundElements":[],"y":-340.03515625,"opacity":100,"height":80,"width":888,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":2046112147},{"seed":416628733,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"botsXrOeKPQdqMm76eyEb","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Key insight: The architectural pattern is always shard the bottleneck.\nV1 had one of everything. Every upgrade adds exactly one partition\nboundary at the point of failure. The final system is V1 with\npartitioning applied at every layer that actually mattered.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6r","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Key insight: The architectural pattern is always shard the bottleneck.\nV1 had one of everything. Every upgrade adds exactly one partition\nboundary at the point of failure. The final system is V1 with\npartitioning applied at every layer that actually mattered.","height":65,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#9AA0B4","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":811509021,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-418,"angle":0,"y":-330.03515625,"width":444.846435546875},{"seed":730216541,"strokeStyle":"dashed","id":"PYNishXRu38KvRVU4mVDi","strokeWidth":1,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"startBinding":null,"endArrowhead":null,"opacity":100,"updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"points":[[0,0],[3000,0]],"polygon":false,"version":5,"type":"line","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6s","roundness":null,"lastCommittedPoint":null,"height":0,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":102729523,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-2424,"angle":0,"y":7.96484375,"width":3000},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#C47B3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b6t","backgroundColor":"#C47B3A","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":2,"version":5,"roundness":null,"type":"ellipse","updated":1773066850103,"id":"4fCPzfEdvoSqMWHVivzGs","x":-2402,"seed":1111041213,"boundElements":[],"y":51.96484375,"opacity":100,"height":40,"width":40,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":317061501},{"seed":1888453917,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"Q-GjsO1sZahDmeT5mRtgV","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":20,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"7","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b6u","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"