ight":1950,"link":null,"startArrowhead":null,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"endBinding":null,"versionNonce":1968216755,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-464,"angle":0,"y":107.96484375,"width":0},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b9L","backgroundColor":"#1E2030","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1.5,"version":5,"roundness":{"type":3},"type":"rectangle","updated":1773066850103,"id":"gCS_Ce03hT96v7yZA5fIx","x":-444,"seed":109604285,"boundElements":[],"y":107.96484375,"opacity":100,"height":1950,"width":920,"frameId":null,"strokeStyle":"solid","versionNonce":966909437},{"seed":1577954845,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"TtvjpYwY3mcAVnhJ4_ZnK","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"FR1: Trigger Execution - How It Works","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9M","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"FR1: Trigger Execution - How It Works","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":275827795,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":125.96484375,"width":285.434814453125},{"seed":667673213,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"55do-dSks_pqOBhljBQmk","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"The scheduler time-wheel fires a tick every second. For each due\njob it attempts Redis SET NX with key job_id:fire_time and TTL 5m.\nOnly one scheduler node wins the lock. The winner publishes to\nKafka partition job_id mod 32. A worker consumes, executes, and\nwrites to execution_log. The UNIQUE idempotency_key column in\nCassandra is a second defense against double-write on worker crash.\nIf Redis is unavailable the scheduler falls back to a Postgres\nadvisory lock -- 10x slower but always correct.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9N","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"The scheduler time-wheel fires a tick every second. For each due\njob it attempts Redis SET NX with key job_id:fire_time and TTL 5m.\nOnly one scheduler node wins the lock. The winner publishes to\nKafka partition job_id mod 32. A worker consumes, executes, and\nwrites to execution_log. The UNIQUE idempotency_key column in\nCassandra is a second defense against double-write on worker crash.\nIf Redis is unavailable the scheduler falls back to a Postgres\nadvisory lock -- 10x slower but always correct.","height":130,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":84874845,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":149.96484375,"width":443.10455322265625},{"seed":411339485,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"TWpIJ32-mm1GNOY7p6fsm","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"What Can Go Wrong (FR1)","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9O","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What Can Go Wrong (FR1)","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1742326259,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":323.96484375,"width":190.78492736816406},{"seed":1355360061,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"-NK6Wl_Z3l2hin4bMJfY_","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Most likely failure: Redis evicts the idempotency key before TTL\ndue to memory pressure. This allows a second scheduler to fire the\nsame job. Defense: Redis maxmemory-policy must be noeviction for\nthe lock keyspace. Worker crash after Kafka commit but before\nCassandra write causes a lost execution record; recover by replaying\nfrom the Kafka offset stored in the consumer group coordinator.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9P","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Most likely failure: Redis evicts the idempotency key before TTL\ndue to memory pressure. This allows a second scheduler to fire the\nsame job. Defense: Redis maxmemory-policy must be noeviction for\nthe lock keyspace. Worker crash after Kafka commit but before\nCassandra write causes a lost execution record; recover by replaying\nfrom the Kafka offset stored in the consumer group coordinator.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1928741565,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":347.96484375,"width":434.91448974609375},{"seed":1660630941,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"ITHsy-Ivzev_eB7twO3hv","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"FR1 Latency Budget","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9Q","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"FR1 Latency Budget","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":278008723,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":485.96484375,"width":149.27992248535156},{"seed":424426493,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"P3Vr-MxBuyAPB2eRjCHMs","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"T+0ms tick. T+50ms Redis SET NX roundtrip. T+52ms Kafka publish\nack. T+200ms Worker poll and dequeue. T+1000ms job executes.\nT+1050ms Cassandra write. Kafka consumer poll interval must be\nunder 50ms. Total p99 budget 1050ms fits within the 1s NFR.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9R","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"T+0ms tick. T+50ms Redis SET NX roundtrip. T+52ms Kafka publish\nack. T+200ms Worker poll and dequeue. T+1000ms job executes.\nT+1050ms Cassandra write. Kafka consumer poll interval must be\nunder 50ms. Total p99 budget 1050ms fits within the 1s NFR.","height":65,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":133751581,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":509.96484375,"width":434.68048095703125},{"seed":2076030045,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"3hb5Rl6IIRwqCtGU2vBrA","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"FR2: Leader Election - How It Works","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9S","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"FR2: Leader Election - How It Works","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":986720563,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":617.96484375,"width":271.28985595703125},{"seed":371269821,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"ly-X7jc4P1v_E_BmlosKU","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Each scheduler node registers an ephemeral ZooKeeper znode at\n\/scheduler\/nodes\/{node_id} on startup. The cluster lists all\nnodes and sorts lexicographically. Node at position i owns\npartitions [i*K, (i+1)*K). On crash, ZK expires the session\nafter 3 seconds. Remaining nodes detect the watch event,\nrecompute ownership, and each loads its new partition range from\nPostgres into its time-wheel. A fencing token from ZK prevents a\nzombie old leader from publishing after losing its session. Ops\ncan force failover by deleting a znode from the ZK shell.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9T","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Each scheduler node registers an ephemeral ZooKeeper znode at\n\/scheduler\/nodes\/{node_id} on startup. The cluster lists all\nnodes and sorts lexicographically. Node at position i owns\npartitions [i*K, (i+1)*K). On crash, ZK expires the session\nafter 3 seconds. Remaining nodes detect the watch event,\nrecompute ownership, and each loads its new partition range from\nPostgres into its time-wheel. A fencing token from ZK prevents a\nzombie old leader from publishing after losing its session. Ops\ncan force failover by deleting a znode from the ZK shell.","height":146.25,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":948467581,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":641.96484375,"width":416.67559814453125},{"seed":2115502365,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"P97TahqwGjOHEnWtbT3Z5","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"What Can Go Wrong (FR2)","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9U","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"What Can Go Wrong (FR2)","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1274710739,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":825.96484375,"width":194.87992858886719},{"seed":420730237,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"vMqGxW-dkyEOZZ_ISzuqp","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"ZooKeeper unavailability blocks all leader changes. Active leaders\nkeep firing but failover is impossible; a crash leaves partitions\nsilent. Mitigation: 5-node ZK ensemble, cross-AZ. The 3-second\nsession timeout sets the recovery window; reducing it below 1s\nrisks false evictions under JVM GC pauses. The fencing token must\nbe checked on every Kafka publish -- stale tokens are rejected.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9V","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"ZooKeeper unavailability blocks all leader changes. Active leaders\nkeep firing but failover is impossible; a crash leaves partitions\nsilent. Mitigation: 5-node ZK ensemble, cross-AZ. The 3-second\nsession timeout sets the recovery window; reducing it below 1s\nrisks false evictions under JVM GC pauses. The fencing token must\nbe checked on every Kafka publish -- stale tokens are rejected.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1860599773,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":849.96484375,"width":427.40057373046875},{"seed":576069085,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"EGplvZ51TehzxqTx9guNN","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"FR3: DAG Dependencies - How It Works","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9W","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"FR3: DAG Dependencies - How It Works","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":950515827,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":997.96484375,"width":292.3048095703125},{"seed":1894799933,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"OkHvVU1myrPFLL2E2Xkft","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"When Job A completes, its worker writes SUCCESS to execution_log.\nThe DAG Resolver polls execution_log every 200ms for new completions.\nFor each completed job it queries job_dag_edge for downstream jobs.\nFor each downstream it increments upstream_done in dag_run_state.\nWhen upstream_done equals upstream_total the downstream job is\nenqueued into the scheduler. If Job A fails, the resolver marks all\ntransitive descendants as BLOCKED and emits an alert. On operator\nretry the resolver clears BLOCKED state and re-checks counts.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9X","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"When Job A completes, its worker writes SUCCESS to execution_log.\nThe DAG Resolver polls execution_log every 200ms for new completions.\nFor each completed job it queries job_dag_edge for downstream jobs.\nFor each downstream it increments upstream_done in dag_run_state.\nWhen upstream_done equals upstream_total the downstream job is\nenqueued into the scheduler. If Job A fails, the resolver marks all\ntransitive descendants as BLOCKED and emits an alert. On operator\nretry the resolver clears BLOCKED state and re-checks counts.","height":130,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1361345597,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":21.96484375,"width":461.8634033203125},{"seed":2109999773,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"6RU2TebqiFYMkTyigdjlM","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":15,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Data Model Decision (FR3)","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9Y","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Data Model Decision (FR3)","height":18.75,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":513683987,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":1169.96484375,"width":198.65989685058594},{"seed":696430333,"strokeStyle":"solid","id":"mg50wrxXTfq1K7lD9Qygi","strokeWidth":2,"roughness":1,"isDeleted":false,"fontSize":13,"opacity":100,"verticalAlign":"top","updated":1773066850103,"locked":false,"text":"Edges are stored separately from job definitions because DAG\nstructure changes far less frequently and needs different access\npatterns. Inline edge storage would require scanning all jobs to\nfind downstream dependents. dag_run_state is keyed by (job_id,\ndag_run_id) not job_id alone to support parameterized DAG runs\nwhere the same DAG fires multiple times concurrently.","version":5,"autoResize":true,"type":"text","backgroundColor":"transparent","index":"b9Z","roundness":null,"containerId":null,"originalText":"Edges are stored separately from job definitions because DAG\nstructure changes far less frequently and needs different access\npatterns. Inline edge storage would require scanning all jobs to\nfind downstream dependents. dag_run_state is keyed by (job_id,\ndag_run_id) not job_id alone to support parameterized DAG runs\nwhere the same DAG fires multiple times concurrently.","height":97.5,"link":null,"strokeColor":"#E2E4ED","fillStyle":"solid","groupIds":[],"versionNonce":1193536669,"textAlign":"left","fontFamily":5,"lineHeight":1.25,"frameId":null,"boundElements":[],"x":-428,"angle":0,"y":1193.96484375,"width":416.35052490234375},{"isDeleted":false,"locked":false,"strokeColor":"#2A2D3A","link":null,"roughness":1,"groupIds":[],"index":"b9a","backgroundColor":"#252838","angle":0,"fillStyle":"solid","strokeWidth":1,"version":5,"roundne